classkit-tool(8)             System Manager's Manual            classkit-tool(8)

NAME
     classkit-tool â€“ ClassKit Tool

SYNOPSIS
     classkit-tool -h | --help
     classkit-tool -s | --show-devmode
     classkit-tool -d | --devmode dev-mode
     classkit-tool -r | --reset-devmode-data

DESCRIPTION
     This tool allows you to test your ClassKit enabled app by putting this Mac
     into development mode, in the role of either teacher or student.  You also
     set the value of the ClassKit entitlement of your application to
     development.  For more information, see
     https://developer.apple.com/documentation/classkit.

     The options are as follows:

     -h | --help                               Show this message and exit.

     -s | --show-devmode                       Return the current development
                                               mode.

     -d | --devmode <off | teacher | student>  Set the development mode to off,
                                               teacher, or student

     -r | --reset-devmode-data                 Reset the development mode data.

HISTORY
     The classkit-tool utility first appeared in macOS 11.

